	<h2>Description</h2>

<p>Free Craft Pricing Calculator for pricing crafts especially keepsake, me=
morial and breastmilk jewellery. <a href=3D"https://keepsakersupplies.com/p=
roduct/lucky-dip-mystery-bags/">Lucky Dip Mystery Bags</a> of silicone moul=
ds (<a href=3D"https://keepsakersupplies.com/product-category/end-of-line-s=
ale/end-of-line-sale-moulds/">end of line moulds</a> and second quality), t=
ools and equipment and sparkles =E2=80=93 containing clear silicone moulds =
and a combination of other items =E2=80=93 you might even get <a href=3D"ht=
tps://keepsakersupplies.com/product-category/end-of-line-sale/end-of-line-s=
ale-settings/">solid silver end of line settings</a> included! Any combinat=
ion of cabochons (oval, round, heart, teardrop etc), spheres, charm beads a=
nd kawaii moulds, tools and equipment, settings, consumables such as breast=
milk preservation powder and freebies.</p>
<h4>Free Craft Pricing Calculator Contents</h4>
<p>Free download, not for resale or redistribution. Please read our full <a=
 href=3D"https://keepsakersupplies.com/terms-and-conditions/" target=3D"_bl=
ank" rel=3D"noopener">Terms and Conditions</a> and FAQ page before ordering=
. If you=E2=80=99re unhappy with the contents of your Free Craft Pricing Ca=
lculator then please delete the file or provide feedback.</p>
<h3>Using Free Craft Pricing Calculator</h3>
<p>To use a Free Craft Pricing Calculator just download then open with your=
 chosen software such as Microsoft Excel or Google Sheets. We do not provid=
e soft service (usage advice) on free items sorry.</p>
<p>Simply mix your resin with colours, sparkles, flowers or your clients=E2=
=80=99 elements or inclusions like <a href=3D"https://keepsakersupplies.com=
/making-breastmilk-jewellery-part-1/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener">br=
eastmilk</a>, <a href=3D"https://keepsakersupplies.com/make-lock-hair-jewel=
lery/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener">lock of hair</a>, <a href=3D"http=
s://keepsakersupplies.com/making-umbilical-cord-jewellery/" target=3D"_blan=
k" rel=3D"noopener">umbilical cord and placenta</a> or <a href=3D"https://k=
eepsakersupplies.com/how-to-make-cremation-ash-jewellery-part-1-of-2/" targ=
et=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener">cremation ashes</a>. Then add to the mould a=
nd cure in the usual way. Or you can add your resin to the mould before add=
ing elements.</p>
<p>If working with UV resin we recommend you work in layers to achieve beau=
tiful depths of colour.</p>
<p>Our moulds are suitable for use with resin (UV resin, EcoResin, epoxy re=
sin or polyester resin), concrete, polymer clay (air drying, heat curing su=
ch as Premo and Sculpey). We recommend removing the polymer clay from the m=
ould before baking if not using air drying clay although they can be heated=
 up to 130=C2=B0C. Although we use a food-safe silicone, we don=E2=80=99t r=
ecommend these moulds for use with food due to the manufacturing process. c=
raft pricing calculator will help you calculate what to charge</p>
<h3>craft pricing calculator Mould Life and Care</h3>
<p>These moulds are sold for semi-permanent use and will degrade with use. =
This is normal and not classed as a fault. Please see our mould care inform=
ation for more info. The life of your moulds will depend on the material us=
ed, the number of uses, how gentle you are using it, good storage, careful =
washing and environmental factors.</p>
<h3>Test Cast</h3>
<p>It is very important you do a test cast with each mould to check for imp=
erfections, to remove any dust attained during transit and to make sure you=
 are comfortable using the mould before making any jewellery. We advise you=
 use UV resin for this and coat the depression in resin before curing, remo=
ving and making a visual check. If there is a problem with the test cast pl=
ease get in touch within 7 days of receipt.</p>
<h3>Settings and Findings</h3>
<p>We recommend that resin cabochons are glued into place and ideally prote=
cted with a rubover bezel. Due to differences in manufacturing processes, w=
e cannot guarantee a perfect fit. If you are unsure please order a single m=
ould to test, make a test cast cabochon (see above) then test it in the bez=
el cup. To help you remove it from the bezel cup, place a length of dental =
floss over the bezel cup first before pushing in the cabochon.</p>
<h3>Contact Us</h3>
<p>If you have any questions please email us on keepsakersupplies@gmail.com=
 or get in touch on our Facebook page <a href=3D"https://www.facebook.com/K=
eepsakerSupplies/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"nofollow noopener">Keepsaker Su=
pplies (click here)</a>.</p>
